track_notes: The eastern approach is much easier but still requires a bushwhack to avoid a large loop.

The gate on Meeting House Mountain road was open which permitted us to drive 1/4 mile and park before beginning our hike on a FS2520. At Big Branch, we followed a faint trail for .1 mile and began a BW up the ridgeline crossing an overgrown road and again up the ridgeline where we intersected FS2541. We continued and took FS2541A to the base of the summit and BW again to summit.  Dean ~ K2JB
